Append new rows of data to the end of a Google Sheet. I'll provide:
1. Spreadsheet ID or name (if name, search for it first)
2. Range indicating the sheet and columns (like "Sheet1!A:C" or "A:C")
3. Data to append (as a table, CSV, or structured format)

Use the append_data tool with these parameters:
- value_input_option: "USER_ENTERED" (interpret formulas and formats)
- insert_data_option: "INSERT_ROWS" (add new rows rather than overwrite)

Before appending:
- Show me the target sheet and column range
- Display a preview of the data that will be added
- Confirm the append operation

After appending:
- Report how many rows were added
- Show the range where data was inserted
- Provide web link to view the updated sheet

This is perfect for adding new records to existing data tables without overwriting anything.